elican and the agile monkey set out to prove that they are the best windowcleaning company around.',2001,3.81,32,16265,32.15,'fantasy'),(814,9780140620122,'Wuthering Heights',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bK-LRAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','In a house haunted by memories, the past is everywhere ... As darkness falls, a man caught in a snowstorm is forced to shelter at the strange, grim house Wuthering Heights. It is a place he will never forget. There he will come to learn the story of Cathy how she was forced to choose between her wellmeaning husband and the dangerous man she had loved since she was young. How her choice led to betrayal and terrible revenge  and continues to torment those in the present. How love can transgress authority, convention, even death. And how desire can kill.',1994,3.84,279,2101,40.65,'science_fiction'),(815,9780140620221,'Pride and Prejudice',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xdySuAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','First published in 1813.',1994,4.25,299,1852,96.8,'fantasy'),(817,9780141014081,'Complete Maus',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rBj-nQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Combined here are Maus I A Survivors Tale and Maus II  the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitlers Europe. By addressing the Holocaust through cartoons the author captures the everyday reality of fear and the sensation of survival.',2003,4.55,296,100212,19.77,'science_fiction'),(819,9780140620634,'Dracula',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0fbAkQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Irish author Bram Stoker introduced the character of Count Dracula and provided the basis of modern vampire fiction in his 1897 novel entitled Dracula. Written as a series of letters, newspaper clippings, diary entries, and ships logs, the story begins with lawyer Jonathan Harker journeying to 