n prairies in 1875 to intermarry among the Cheyenne Indians. The covert and controversial Brides for Indians program, launched by the administration of Ulysses S. Grant, is intended to help assimilate the Indians into the white mans world. Toward that end May and her friends embark upon the adventure of their lifetime. Jim Fergus has so vividly depicted the American West that it is as if these diaries are a capsule in time.',1999,3.88,434,97955,98.01,'fantasy'),(1411,9780312203030,'High Five',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9aqX3Z1vlLkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','New Jersey bounty hunter Stephanie Plum struggles to make ends meet while coping with a missing Uncle Fred, homicidal rapist and stalker Benito Ramirez, amorous vice cop Joe Morelli, and wouldbe lover Roger',1999,4.18,292,660,58.9,'thriller'),(1412,9780312203856,'James Tiptree Jr','The Double Life of Alice B Sheldon','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TNdL3H0tgKsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Profiles the successful woman author who hid behind the male pen name of James Tiptree, Jr., to publish short works of science fiction in the 1970s, describing her work as an intelligence officer during World War II and her shocking suicide.',2006,4.24,469,929,48.75,'action_adventure'),(1413,9780312241223,'Birds of America','Stories','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pLBTgtXCPkkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','A National Book Critics Circle Award Finalist A New York Times Editors Choice A Pulishers Weekly Best Book of the Year Birds of America is a stunning collection of twelve stories by Lorrie Moore, one of our finest authors at work today. With her characteristic wit and piercing intelligence she unfolds a series of portraits of the lost and unsettled of America, and with a trademark humor that fuels each story with pathos and understanding.',1999,4.11,291,11984,57.04,'fantasy'),(1414,9780312241353,'And The Band Played on','