ds spreading throughout the galaxy, threatening to stifle all human endeavor, and the hidden group of rebels who try to stem the humanoid tide, if it is not already too late',1996,3.75,299,880,71.29,'science_fiction'),(1529,9780312853020,'The Demon Princes Vol 1','The Star King  The Killing Machine  The Palace of Love','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=L2nkDav2B-oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Collects three of the authors novels about the Demon Princes, a destructive race of beings who disguise themselves as humans, and Kerth Gersen, who is out to avenge himself for the destruction of his world',1997,4.25,446,1109,94.36,'thriller'),(1531,9780312861872,'Xenocide','Volume Three of the Ender Quintet','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=T2AfTwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','The war for survival of the planet Lusitania will be fought in the heart of a child named Gloriously Bright. On Lusitania, Ender found a world where humans and pequininos and the Hive Queen could all live together where three very different intelligent species could find common ground at last. Or so he thought. Lusitania also harbors the descolada, a virus that kills all humans it infects, but which the pequininos require in order to become adults. The Startways Congress so fears the effects of the descolada, should it escape from Lusitania, that they have ordered the destruction of the entire planet, and all who live there. The Fleet is on its way, a second xenocide seems inevitable. Xenocide is the third novel in Orson Scott Cards Ender Quintet.',1996,3.79,592,115661,46.45,'fantasy'),(1532,9780312862176,'The Dark Descent',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pNgZxdPETK0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','Traces the evolution of the horror story by presenting an anthology of works from the past and from current writers, with contributions from Stephen King, H.P. Lovecraft, Harlan Ellison, Charles L. Grant, and Cli